com.gemalto.mfs.mwsdk.cdcvm

Class DeviceCVMVerifierInput

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.gemalto.mfs.mwsdk.cdcvm.DeviceCVMVerifierInput

  • public class DeviceCVMVerifierInput
extends Object
    A class that contains information used for starting biometric authentication.

    This is applicable only from Android 6.0 onwards and if CHVerificationMethod is BIOMETRICS.

    • Constructor Detail

      • DeviceCVMVerifierInput

        public DeviceCVMVerifierInput(CharSequence title,
                              CharSequence subtitle,
                              CharSequence description,
                              CharSequence negativeButtonText)
        Creates a DeviceCVMVerifierInput with the specified title, subtitle, description and negative button text.

        Notes:

        • title, subtitle, description and negative button text are only used when OS version is >= Android Q when displaying the unified biometric prompt dialog.
        • A DeviceCVMCancellationSignal will also be created, which can be used to cancel the biometric authentication process.

        See Also:
        BiometricPrompt.Builder#setTitle(CharSequence), BiometricPrompt.Builder#setSubtitle(CharSequence), BiometricPrompt.Builder#setDescription(CharSequence), BiometricPrompt.Builder#setNegativeButton(CharSequence, Executor, OnClickListener)
